  "doc_id": "9017",
  "text": "Although temperature rise of electric machines can be reduced by the two aforementioned approaches, the selection of solving domain has been ignored and not been deeply studied in the previous research. Generally, partial solving domain will be selected to analyze by researchers in order to save the calculation time, such as 1/48 of the whole machine [CITATION_1] , 1/36 along the circumferential direction of the structure [CITATION_2] and half an axial segment along the axial direction of the machine [CITATION_3] . It should be noted that the different solving domain cause different simulation results. How to select a suitable domain has not been properly discussed yet.",
